EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 082300 UTC
DURING WEDNESDAY EVENING AND THURSDAY AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE 1036 WILL
LIE E OF ICELAND WITH A RIDGE EXTENDING SWARDS ACROSS THE UK AND BAY OF
BISCAY LINKING TO THE AZORES HIGH PRESSURE. A COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE
980 WILL REMAIN IN THE MID ATLANTIC WITH FRONTAL TROUGHS APPROACHING SHANNON
ROCKALL AND BAILEY.
A SMALL LEE LOW PRESSURE AREA WILL FORM W OF NORWAY. A SIMILAR PRESSURE
PATTERN WILL PERSIST THROUGH FRIDAY AND SATURDAY WITH THE HIGH PRESSURE AREA
REMAINING OVER SCANDINAVIA AND DEEP LOW PRESSURE AREAS CONTINUING IN THE
MID ATLANTIC WITH FRONTAL TROUGHS REMAINING W OF IRELAND. DURING WEDNESDAY
EVENING AND THURSDAY MORNING NE WINDS WILL BE STRG AT TIMES IN THAMES DOVER
